{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.20",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 20 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:1",
      "text": "How much better is it to reprove, than to be angry, and not to hinder him that confesseth in prayer.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:2",
      "text": "The lust of an eunuch shall deflour a young maiden:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:3",
      "text": "So is he that by violence executeth of the unwise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:4",
      "text": "How good is it, when thou art reproved, to shew repentance! for so thou shalt escape wilful sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:5",
      "text": "There is one that holdeth his peace, that is found wise: and there is another that is hateful, that is bold in speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:6",
      "text": "There is one that holdeth his peace, because he knoweth not what to say: and there is another that holdeth his peace, knowing the proper time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:7",
      "text": "A wise man will hold his peace till he see opportunity: but a babbler, and a fool, will regard no time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:8",
      "text": "He that useth many words shall hurt his own soul: and he that taketh authority to himself unjustly shall be hated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:9",
      "text": "There is success in evil things to a man without discipline, and there is a finding that turneth to loss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:10",
      "text": "There is a gift that is not profitable: and there is a gift, the recompense of which is double.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:11",
      "text": "There is an abasement because of glory: and there is one that shall lift up his head from a low estate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:12",
      "text": "There is that buyeth much for a small price, and restoreth the same sevenfold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:13",
      "text": "A man wise in words shall make himself beloved: but the graces of fools shall be poured out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:14",
      "text": "The gift of the fool shall do thee no good: for his eyes are sevenfold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:15",
      "text": "He will give a few things, and upbraid much: and the opening of his mouth is the kindling of a fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:16",
      "text": "To day a man lendeth, and to morrow he asketh it again: such a man as this is hateful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:17",
      "text": "A fool shall have no friend, and there shall be no thanks for his good deeds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:18",
      "text": "For they that eat his bread, are of a false tongue. How often, and how many will laugh him to scorn!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:19",
      "text": "For he doth not distribute with right understanding that which was to be had: in like manner also that which was not to be had.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:20",
      "text": "The slipping of a false tongue is as one that falleth on the pavement: so the fall of the wicked shall come speedily.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:21",
      "text": "A man without grace is as a vain fable, it shall be continually in the mouth of the unwise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:22",
      "text": "A parable coming out of a fool's mouth shall be rejected: for he doth not speak it in due season.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:23",
      "text": "There is that is hindered from sinning through want, and in his rest he shall be pricked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:24",
      "text": "There is that will destroy his own soul through shamefacedness, and by occasion of an unwise person he will destroy it: and by respect of person he will destroy himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:25",
      "text": "There is that for bashfulness promiseth to his friend, and maketh him his enemy for nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:26",
      "text": "A lie is a foul blot in a man, and yet it will be continually in the mouth of men without discipline.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:27",
      "text": "A thief is better than a man that is always lying: but both of them shall inherit destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:28",
      "text": "The manners of lying men are without honour: and their confusion is with them without ceasing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:29",
      "text": "A wise man shall advance himself with his words, and a prudent man shall please the great ones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:30",
      "text": "He that tilleth his land shall make a high heap of corn: and he that worketh justice shall be exalted: and he that pleaseth great men shall escape iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:31",
      "text": "Presents and gifts blind the eyes of judges, and make them dumb in the mouth, so that they cannot correct.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:32",
      "text": "O Wisdom that is hid, and treasure that is not seen: what profit is there in them both?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.20.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:33",
      "text": "Better is he that hideth his folly, than the man that hideth his wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
